China frees Hong Kong journalist Xi Yang . China on Saturday released on parole Hong Kong journalist Xi Yang , who had been serving a 12 - year prison term for stealing state secrets , the official Xinhua news agency said . Xi , a former reporter for Hong Kong ' s Chinese - language Ming Pao newspaper , was released with 157 days to go before the British colony reverts to Chinese rule on July 1 , 1997 . He left Beijing for Hong Kong on Saturday evening , Xinhua said . Xi was paroled because he " showed signs of repentance " , the agency said . China jailed Xi for 12 years in 1994 for stealing state secrets about internal policies on interest rates and gold . The severity of the sentence shocked Hong Kong reporters , already pessimistic about the prospects for a free press after the handover and triggered protests in the British colony . 
